text: Ahmed Al Ahmed is a Syrian player born in 18 October 1996. He plays for Al- Ittihad in Syrian Premier League. He started his career with Al-Hurriya before he joined Al-Ittihad. In 14 January 2019, he joined Damac, Saudi division 1 team. Which he considered as big step in order to play for the biggest teams in the future. His older brother Mohammad plays for Al-Ittihad. ==International Career== He got his first cap on 20 March 2019 against Iraq in 2019 International Friendship Championship. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Syrian footballers Category:Syrian expatriate footballers Category:Syria international footballers Category:Association football midfielders Category:People from Aleppo Category:Syrian expatriate sportspeople in Saudi Arabia Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players Category:Al-Ittihad Aleppo players Category:Hurriya SC players Category:Damac FC players Category:Syrian Premier League players
